<a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/most-say-new-zealand-is-on-the-wrong-track-can-it-avoid-a-drift-to-populism" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/picture/2023/aug/08/ella-baron-on-the-uncertainty-facing-arrivals-to-the-uk-cartoon" target="_blank">Ella Baron on the uncertainty facing arrivals to the UK – cartoon</a></h2><div class="description"> The Duchess of Cambridge and Prince Eugenia will be knighted in the Queen of England. She will be joined by the Queen Elizabeth II in a bid to woo the country's most powerful politician. The Queen is expected to be crowned queen of the United Kingdom in May 2015.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 19:00:35 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/picture/2023/aug/08/ella-baron-on-the-uncertainty-facing-arrivals-to-the-uk-cartoon" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/08/sinead-o-connor-mental-illness-mainstream-debate" target="_blank">Forget Instagram influencers, Sinéad O’Connor showed mental illness as it truly is | Hannah Jane Parkinson</a></h2><div class="description"> Sinéad O’Connor, who died last month at 56, went missing in March 2016. The Telegraph ran a live blog on the singer’s whereabouts after she had posted suicidal thoughts. I pointed out to an editor at the paper that rolling updates about a person going through a severe mental health episode, an episode that might have ended fatally, was a mistake.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 12:16:16 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/08/sinead-o-connor-mental-illness-mainstream-debate" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/08/immigration-lawyer-braverman-smear-campaign-rightwing-press-deported-to-rwanda" target="_blank">I’m an immigration lawyer, and now the target of a Braverman smear campaign. It will backfire  | Jacqueline McKenzie</a></h2><div class="description"> Government has set the rightwing press on me because I have represented someone being deported to Rwanda - but I know people can see through their deception. I was followed on social media by journalists from the Sun and the Daily Mail within minutes of each other. I immediately thought this to be a government-inspired hit job because of my work supporting victims of the Windrush scandal.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 16:00:31 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/08/immigration-lawyer-braverman-smear-campaign-rightwing-press-deported-to-rwanda" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/08/its-almost-18-months-since-russia-invaded-ukraine-and-peace-seems-no-closer" target="_blank">It’s almost 18 months since Russia invaded Ukraine, and peace seems no closer | Rajan Menon</a></h2><div class="description"> Initiatives aimed at ending the war that Russia started by invading Ukraine have been underway for months. On 24 February – a year to the day Russia started its attack – China unveiled a proposal containing 12 principles. In June, a group of African leaders met separately with Ukrainian president Volodymyr Zelenskiy and Russian president Vladimir Putin to present a peace plan.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 10:13:22 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/08/its-almost-18-months-since-russia-invaded-ukraine-and-peace-seems-no-closer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/08/refugee-barges-sewage-e-coli-why-would-anyone-like-to-be-beside-the-seaside" target="_blank">Refugee barges! Sewage! E coli! Why would anyone like to be beside the seaside? | Zoe Williams</a></h2><div class="description"> Dorset is mainly in the news because of the giant refugee barge that has just taken delivery of its first residents. Even if you couldn’t see it from your beach hut – it would be charming to go to a Dorset beach when the area is.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 10:00:33 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/08/refugee-barges-sewage-e-coli-why-would-anyone-like-to-be-beside-the-seaside" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class