-to-be-given-two-weeks-to-explain-closing-of-customer-accounts" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/08/mould-found-in-lungs-of-oldham-man-who-died-in-house-with-chronic-damp-inquest-hears" target="_blank">Mould found in lungs of man who died in house with chronic damp, inquest hears</a></h2><div class="description"> Luke Brooks, 27, of Oldham, died from respiratory problems caused by aspergillus pneumonia. Family believe mould in their privately rented end of terrace house in Oldham caused his death. Pathologist says mould was found in the lungs of a man who died in a house that had chronic damp.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 17:12:14 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/08/mould-found-in-lungs-of-oldham-man-who-died-in-house-with-chronic-damp-inquest-hears" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/08/england-to-deny-covid-and-flu-jabs-to-under-65s-amid-fears-for-nhs-this-winter" target="_blank">England to deny Covid and flu jabs to under-65s despite fears for NHS this winter</a></h2><div class="description"> Government accepts advice from JCVI which says only at-risk groups and those aged 65 and over should be offered vaccines. Millions of people under the age of 65 in England will be denied flu and Covid jabs this winter despite one of the government’s top public health officials warning that coronavirus has not “gone away”</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 13:18:24 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">health</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/08/england-to-deny-covid-and-flu-jabs-to-under-65s-amid-fears-for-nhs-this-winter" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/08/humza-yousaf-says-he-believes-nicola-sturgeons-resignation-was-genuine" target="_blank">Humza Yousaf: I don’t believe Sturgeon knew arrests pending before resignation</a></h2><div class="description"> Scotland’s first minister admits ‘everybody’ wondered whether his predecessor anticipated direction of police investigation. Humza Yousaf also admitted he felt ‘a little bit” las if he had ended up answering for issues around party transparency that were not his fault.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 18:12:13 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/08/humza-yousaf-says-he-believes-nicola-sturgeons-resignation-was-genuine" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/aug/08/target-of-tory-lefty-lawyer-dossier-forced-to-review-security-after-email" target="_blank">Target of Tory ‘lefty lawyer’ dossier forced to review security after email</a></h2><div class="description"> Jacqueline McKenzie, head of immigration at Leigh Day, says she has had to take precautions after ‘ominous’ message. She said briefing sent to the Telegraph, Mail, Sun and Express by party officials was “underpinned by racism and misogyny”</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 16:00:31 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/aug/08/target-of-tory-lefty-lawyer-dossier-forced-to-review-security-after-email" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/08/man-jailed-for-10-years-for-raping-girl-who-was-later-murdered-by-her-brother" target="_blank">Man jailed for 10 years for raping girl who was later murdered by her brother</a></h2><div class="description"> Jamie Starrs, 20, was sentenced for his assault on Amber Gibson, 16, who was killed five months later. Amber Gibson was sexually assaulted and murdered by her older brother, Connor Gibson, in June 2021. Amber was raped while she was incapacitated at a property in Bothwell, South Lanarkshire.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 16:04:32 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/08/man-jailed-for-10-years-for-raping-girl-who-was-later-murdered-by-her-brother" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/aug/08/fears-over-antarctic-sea-ice-as-yearly-ozone-layer-hole-forms-very-early" target="_blank">Fears over Antarctic sea ice as yearly ozone layer hole forms ‘very early’</a></h2><div class="description"> Experts say larger-than-normal hole could cause further warming of Southern Ocean and heighten damaging effects of 2022 Tonga volcano eruption. The hole in the ozone layer has begun to form early this year, prompting warnings that a larger than average hole may further warm the Southern Ocean.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 15:00:32 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/aug/08/fears-over-antarctic-sea-ice-as-yearly-ozone-layer-hole-forms-very-early" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/aug/09/google-says-ai-systems-should-be-able-to-mine-publishers-work-unless-companies-opt-out" target="_blank">Google says AI systems should be able to mine publishers’ work unless companies opt out</a></h2><div class="description"> Google's latest proposal about generative AI turns copyright law on its head, and could especially hurt smaller content creators, say experts. Publishers should be able to opt out of having their works mined by generative artificial intelligence systems, according to Google, but the compa says.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 23:00:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/aug/09/google-says-ai-systems-should-be-able-to-mine-publishers-work-unless-companies-opt-out" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/08/alabama-riverfront-brawl" target="_blank">Three white men face assault charges in Alabama riverfront brawl</a></h2><div class="description"> One man in custody and two others expected to surrender after a group of white men attacked a Black boat worker in Montgomery, Alabama. Police chief Darryl Albert announced on Tuesday that one man is in custody, two others are expected to turn themselves in. Montgomery mayor Steven Reed said none of the three are residents of the city.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 21:03:36 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/08/alabama-riverfront-brawl" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/storm-hans-causes-havoc-in-norway-with-heaviest-rain-in-25-years-forecast" target="_blank">Storm Hans causes havoc in Norway with heaviest rain in 25 years forecast</a></h2><div class="description"> Storm Hans has killed two people, ripped off roofs and caused widespread disruption across northern Europe in a summer that started with wildfires across much of the region. Forecasters have warned of the strongest rainfall in a quarter of a century. The storm – named Storm Hans – has killed 2 people and has left an entire town stranded.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 15:47:57 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/storm-hans-causes-havoc-in-norway-with-heaviest-rain-in-25-years-forecast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/thailand-king-estranged-son-surprise-return-royal-family-succession-vacharaesorn-vivacharawongse" target="_blank">Thailand king’s estranged son makes surprise return after 27 years</a></h2><div class="description"> Vacharaesorn Vivacharawongse makes what appeared to be a low-key arrival at Suvarnabhumi airport on Sunday. The estranged second son of Thailand’s king has returned to Bangkok for the first time in almost three decades.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 14:50:32 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/thailand-king-estranged-son-surprise-return-royal-family-succession-vacharaesorn-vivacharawongse" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/five-officers-arrested-in-marseille-over-death-of-man-during-riots" target="_blank">Five police officers arrested in Marseille over death of man in riots</a></h2><div class="description"> Mohamed Bendriss went into cardiac arrest, probably after being struck by ‘flash-ball type’ police projectile, prosecutor says. The 27-year-old man died during rioting in the French city on 1 July. Officers were among 20 members of the elite Raid (Research, assistance, intervention, dissuasion) tactical unit.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 14:50:24 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/five-officers-arrested-in-marseille-over-death-of-man-during-riots" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/canada-publishers-protest-meta-blocking-users-news-access" target="_blank">Canada publishers urge Ottawa to stop Meta from blocking users’ news access</a></h2><div class="description"> Meta's decision to bar Canadians from viewing news on Facebook and Instagram amounted to ‘anticompetitive conduct’ and violates a provision of a federal law. News Media Canada, the Canadian Association of Broadcasters and CBC/Radio‐Canada have called on the country’s competition regulator to stop Meta from blocking access to news.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 16:52:42 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/canada-publishers-protest-meta-blocking-users-news-access" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/colombia-cartel-drug-lord-otoniel-jailed" target="_blank">Colombian drug lord and paramilitary leader jailed for 45 years in US</a></h2><div class="description"> Dairo Antonio Úsuga, known as Otoniel, makes apology to US, Colombia ‘and to the victims of the crimes that I have committed’ He was once feared as one of Colombia’s most dangerous drug lords. He has been sentenced to 45 years in prison in the US.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 18:49:52 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/colombia-cartel-drug-lord-otoniel-jailed" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/08/massachusetts-governor-declares-emergency-and-urges-help-for-migrants" target="_blank">Massachusetts governor declares emergency and urges help for migrants</a></h2><div class="description"> Maura Healey calls on federal government to provide ‘urgent action’ as shelters housing migrants and refugees reach capacity. Healey: “To our partners in the federal government, Massachusetts has stepped up to address what sadly has been a federal crisis of inaction that is many years in the making’</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 21:58:08 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/08/massachusetts-governor-declares-emergency-and-urges-help-for-migrants" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/08/sex-robot-courtney-pauroso-vanessa-5000-edinburgh-fringe" target="_blank">‘Like a naughty Siri’: friendly sex robot Vanessa 5000 asks audiences to test her powers</a></h2><div class="description"> LA comic and clown Courtney Pauroso plays a latex-clad humanoid pleasure device in her Edinburgh show. Her solo performances shift sharply from wide-eyed innocence to grotesque, knockout humour. As a kid she would watch I Love Lucy reruns with her grandma, harbouring dreams of becoming an actor.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 15:10:29 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/08/sex-robot-courtney-pauroso-vanessa-5000-edinburgh-fringe" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/books/2023/aug/08/a-smorgasbord-of-unlikability-the-authors-helping-sad-girl-lit-grow-up" target="_blank">‘A smorgasbord of unlikability’: the authors helping ‘sad girl lit’ grow up</a></h2><div class="description"> Post-Fleabag world has become obsessed with the inner turmoils of messy millennials. But isn’t it time they pulled themselves together? Meet the novelists subverting the cliches. Almost always the main character (like the author) will be middle-class, if not incredibly wealthy.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 15:19:43 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/books/2023/aug/08/a-smorgasbord-of-unlikability-the-authors-helping-sad-girl-lit-grow-up" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/08/thousands-gather-funeral-sinead-oconnor-ireland" target="_blank">‘She blazed a trail’: thousands gather for funeral of Sinéad O’Connor in Ireland</a></h2><div class="description"> Thousands pack seafront in Bray, County Wicklow, to bid farewell to singer and celebrate her life. By midday on Tuesday thousands were lining the seafront to greet the funeral cortege. The Irish singer had called home, and died at the age of 56.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 12:42:35 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/08/thousands-gather-funeral-sinead-oconnor-ireland" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/08/chris-noth-denies-sexual-assault-allegations-sex-and-the-city" target="_blank">‘It isn’t a crime’: Chris Noth denies sexual assault allegations in first interview since they were made</a></h2><div class="description"> Chris Noth, best known for playing Mr Big in the HBO series Sex and the City, has given his first interview since sexual assault accusations against him were made public in December 2021. Noth again admitted adultery but denied the allegations made by two women about separate incidents they say took place in 2004 and 2015.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 15:56:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/08/chris-noth-denies-sexual-assault-allegations-sex-and-the-city" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/08/drew-michael-review-pleasance-dome-edinburgh" target="_blank">Drew Michael: Drew’s Adventures review – SNL writer’s spiky and serious comedy</a></h2><div class="description"> Drew Michael’s first televised set was called ‘the most polarising comedy special of the year’ and its follow-up likewise divided audiences. The 37-year-old is stronger on structure and invention than on jokes, which absent themselves entirely as the show narrows to its heartfelt conclusion. Michael interrupts with staged phone-calls from the audience protesting against the show's self-indulgence.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 21:00:37 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/08/drew-michael-review-pleasance-dome-edinburgh" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2023/aug/09/tv-series-like-oppenheimer-manhattan-where-to-watch-stan" target="_blank">Before Oppenheimer, there was Manhattan: this underrated drama is a must-see</a></h2><div class="description"> Despite a starry cast and strong writing, this series about the scientists living and working in Los Alamos was criminally underwatched. Manhattan is streaming on Stan.com. For more recommendations of what to stream in Australia, <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/culture/series/stream-team" click here.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 15:00:32 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2023/aug/09/tv-series-like-oppenheimer-manhattan-where-to-watch-stan" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/nightlife-loveseats-and-beautiful-beaches-why-the-caribbean-makes-for-the-perfect-romantic-holiday" target="_blank">Nightlife, loveseats and beautiful beaches: why the Caribbean makes for the perfect romantic holiday</a></h2><div class="description"> The Caribbean is an unbeatable destination for a romantic getaway. From Jamaica to the hidden gem that is Curaçao, there’s something to suit every couple, whether on honeymoon, celebrating an anniversary, or just escaping. Each of the many islands has its own unique history and vibe – and they all have plenty to offer.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 07 Jun 2023 10:37:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/nightlife-loveseats-and-beautiful-beaches-why-the-caribbean-makes-for-the-perfect-romantic-holiday" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/waterfalls-history-and-the-worlds-first-underwater-sculpture-park-seven-exciting-things-to-do-in-the-caribbean" target="_blank">Waterfalls, history and the world’s first underwater sculpture park: seven exciting things to do in the Caribbean</a></h2><div class="description"> The islands of the Caribbean are like nowhere else on Earth. From cocktails to coral reefs, they offer something for all tastes and tempos. Enjoy sunset cocktails on the white sand beaches of Barbados or Jamaica. Enjoy a classic mojito or piña colada at the heart of the reggae-infused warmth of Jamaica.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 07 Jun 2023 10:36:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/waterfalls-history-and-the-worlds-first-underwater-sculpture-park-seven-exciting-things-to-do-in-the-caribbean" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/from-snorkelling-to-surfing-nine-must-try-caribbean-beach-and-water-activities" target="_blank">From snorkelling to surfing: nine must-try Caribbean beach and water activities</a></h2><div class="description"> The Caribbean offers a huge variety of tempting activities from snorkelling to scuba diving. Windsurfing and waterskiing is a must-try activity for everyone. Scuba diving is a great way to explore the most beautiful coral reefs imaginable. The Caribbean is home to some of the world’s most beautiful, vivid coral reefs.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 07 Jun 2023 10:38:48 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/from-snorkelling-to-surfing-nine-must-try-caribbean-beach-and-water-activities" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/gallery/2023/jun/07/from-pig-beach-to-dunns-river-falls-10-must-visit-caribbean-destinations-in-pictures" target="_blank">From Pig Beach to Dunn’s River Falls: 10 must-visit Caribbean destinations – in pictures</a></h2><div class="description"> The Caribbean is home to the world’s best beaches, pretty towns, waterfalls and national parks. Visit the Caribbean in all its glory. Visit the world's best beaches and waterfalls in the Caribbean. Visit CNN.com/Travel next Friday for more Caribbean travel stories.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 07 Jun 2023 10:35:34 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/gallery/2023/jun/07/from-pig-beach-to-dunns-river-falls-10-must-visit-caribbean-destinations-in-pictures" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/08/tiktok-how-shopping-went-social-hooked-new-generation" target="_blank">‘Where did I get my top? TikTok!’ How shopping went social – and hooked a new generation</a></h2><div class="description"> Zainab Hakim, 23, watches sellers livestream on social media site TikTok, peddling their wares in real time. With a couple of clicks, she can buy things via the app. “I probably have an addiction at this point,” she says. ‘I just get sucked in.”</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 13:00:28 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/08/tiktok-how-shopping-went-social-hooked-new-generation" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/08/the-isometric-secret-15-ways-to-get-much-fitter-without-moving-a-muscle" target="_blank">The isometric secret: 15 ways to get much fitter – without moving a muscle</a></h2><div class="description"> The plank and wall sit are the best exercises to reduce your blood pressure. Here is how to do them – and some other great poses – whatever your current fitness level. Isometrics were most likely to reduce blood pressure, with full-body movements such as the wall squat showing bigger benefits than moves such  moves such as wall squat.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 09:00:04 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/08/the-isometric-secret-15-ways-to-get-much-fitter-without-moving-a-muscle" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2023/aug/08/nigel-slater-midweek-breakfast-grilled-greengages-bircher-muesli-and-maple-syrup" target="_blank">Nigel Slater’s recipe for grilled greengages, bircher muesli and maple syrup</a></h2><div class="description"> An unusual, luxurious take on a healthy fruity breakfast classic. Weigh 250g of greengages and cut each fruit in half. Sugar the fruit generously with 2 tbsp of caster sugar. Cook for 7-10 minutes until soft and lightly caramelised until soft.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 11:01:25 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2023/aug/08/nigel-slater-midweek-breakfast-grilled-greengages-bircher-muesli-and-maple-syrup" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/08/my-partners-vagina-has-atrophied-and-she-is-struggling-to-reach-climax" target="_blank">My partner’s vagina has atrophied – and she is struggling to reach climax</a></h2><div class="description"> Following a hysterectomy, penetration is uncomfortable for her after 15 years of having sex. She has been unable to climax through penetration, which is new for her. Are there ways I can help? Send your story to iReport.com/help@dailymailonline.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 11:13:42 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/08/my-partners-vagina-has-atrophied-and-she-is-struggling-to-reach-climax" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2023/aug/09/easy-and-cheesy-three-savoury-bakes-for-school-lunchboxes-recipes" target="_blank">Easy and cheesy: three savoury bakes for school lunchboxes – recipes</a></h2><div class="description"> Cookbook author George Georgievski AKA School Lunchbox Dad, comes simple cheddar muffins, freezer-friendly frittata slices and a new spin on pizza. Get creative with whatever veggies you like in this recipe for your school lunchesboxed meals.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 15:00:32 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2023/aug/09/easy-and-cheesy-three-savoury-bakes-for-school-lunchboxes-recipes" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2023/aug/08/family-favourites-movie-night-snacks-to-steal-the-show-kitchen-aide-anna-berrill" target="_blank">Family favourites: movie night snacks to steal the show | Kitchen aide</a></h2><div class="description"> Chef Tom Kerridge's 'amazing chocolate popcorn bars' can be made up to a week ahead. Dark chocolate is non-neg, so are ‘perfect for impromptu movie nights with the kids inviting friends over at the last minute’ The snack bars can be kept in the fridge for a week and can easily be made in advance.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 13:00:27 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2023/aug/08/family-favourites-movie-night-snacks-to-steal-the-show-kitchen-aide-anna-berrill" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/13/why-barcelonas-beaches-are-disappearing-video" target="_blank">Why Barcelona’s beaches are disappearing – video</a></h2><div class="description"> In 2010, Barcelona’s nine city beaches were topped up with 700,000 cubic metres of sand. Since then 70% of that sand has disappeared. In the past 20 years the rate of erosion along Spain's east coast has been accelerating. It is partly to do with storms and rising sea levels but there are other factors at play.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 13 Jul 2023 08:46:44 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">tech</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/13/why-barcelonas-beaches-are-disappearing-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jun/22/what-you-need-to-know-about-the-extreme-heatwave-hitting-our-oceans-video-explainer" target="_blank">What you need to know about the 'extreme' heatwave hitting our oceans – video explainer</a></h2><div class="description"> Sea temperatures off the north-east coast of England and west of Ireland are several degrees above normal, breaking records for late spring and early summer. The Met Office said global sea surface temperatures in April and May reached an all-time high, and June is likely to follow suit. Experts said marine heatwaves have a similar impact on the environment as wildfires on land.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 22 Jun 2023 14:22:05 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jun/22/what-you-need-to-know-about-the-extreme-heatwave-hitting-our-oceans-video-explainer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/25/i-was-a-terrorist-now-i-run-a-kindergarten-video" target="_blank">I was a terrorist. Now I run a kindergarten – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Hendi Suhartono was part of a plot to detonate four book bombs and blow up a church in Indonesia. He spent seven years in prison after going through a deradicalisation process. After being released from prison, he received support to open a kindergarten. He meets a friend from his past, Pepi Fernando, and they discuss what led to his radicalisation.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 25 Jul 2023 09:15:15 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/25/i-was-a-terrorist-now-i-run-a-kindergarten-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/video/2023/jul/04/nhs-founder-would-turn-in-his-grave-as-service-faces-crisis-at-75-video" target="_blank">Inside the NHS as staff say future hangs in the balance – video</a></h2><div class="description"> The NHS was launched in 1948 by Labour MP Aneurin Bevan, inspired in part by the Tredegar Medical Aid Society in his constituency. It has since saved the lives of millions and inspired health systems around the world. Seventy-five years on, the Guardian video team was given access to NHS services in south Wales town.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 04 Jul 2023 10:19:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/video/2023/jul/04/nhs-founder-would-turn-in-his-grave-as-service-faces-crisis-at-75-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/19/what-is-supercharging-the-global-heat-video-explainer" target="_blank">What is supercharging the global heat? – video explainer</a></h2><div class="description"> The planet is being hit with a double whammy of global heating in 2023: on top of the rise in global temperature caused by greenhouse gas emissions is an emerging El Niño. This sporadic event is the biggest natural influence on year-to-year weather. The Guardian's environment editor, Damian Carrington, explains what El Niño is and how it affects extreme weather.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 16:48:08 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/19/what-is-supercharging-the-global-heat-video-explainer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/video/2023/jul/28/how-i-survived-a-sex-ed-shitstorm-video" target="_blank">How I survived a 'sex-ed shitstorm' – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Cartoonist Fiona Katauskas's book, The Amazing True Story of How Babies are Made, had been on Kmart and Big W shelves for three years. What started as a debate over the offending picture on Facebook would explode over several days into multiple headlines. Here is her take on what happened.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 27 Jul 2023 15:00:43 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/video/2023/jul/28/how-i-survived-a-sex-ed-shitstorm-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/11/kids-vs-cars-taking-back-play-space-on-british-streets-video" target="_blank">Kids v cars: the campaign to reclaim children's play space on British streets – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Families are campaigning for children to have fun outdoors again. The Guardian’s Harriet Grant travels to Bristol to meet a group that is helping to close streets to cars to reclaim the space on children's doorsteps. Playing Out aims to reclaim play space on the doorsteps of children's front door.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 11 Jul 2023 09:30:38 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/11/kids-vs-cars-taking-back-play-space-on-british-streets-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/2023/aug/08/uk-students-do-you-plan-to-live-at-home-during-university" target="_blank">UK students: do you plan to live at home during university?</a></h2><div class="description"> More than 90% of higher education students are worried about the rising cost of living. We want to speak to students who are living at home this year amid rising costs. Are you planning to commute in? Or are you going to live on campus? Are there other ways you plan on saving costs?</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 12:33:25 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/2023/aug/08/uk-students-do-you-plan-to-live-at-home-during-university" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/08/uk-workers-are-you-struggling-to-get-the-hours-youd-like-to-work" target="_blank">UK workers: are you struggling to get the hours you’d like to work?</a></h2><div class="description"> We want to hear from ‘underemployed’ UK workers who are not getting as much work as they’d like. Whether you’ve had trouble finding full time work, have had shifts cancelled regularly or have had your hours reduced permanently by your employer since you signed up for the job.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 13:27:23 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/08/uk-workers-are-you-struggling-to-get-the-hours-youd-like-to-work" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/03/tell-us-how-have-you-been-impcted-by-extreme-weather-in-britain" target="_blank">Tell us: how have you been impacted by extreme weather in the UK?</a></h2><div class="description"> We want to hear how people have been affected by heatwaves, storms and flooding in the UK in the last few years. Around the world, 2023 has been a year of deadly extreme weather, from wildfires in Greece to deadly heatwaves in India and Canada. We ask people to share their experiences of being affected by extreme weather.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 03 Aug 2023 09:25:53 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/03/tell-us-how-have-you-been-impcted-by-extreme-weather-in-britain" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/08/uk-graduates-share-your-experience-of-applying-for-jobs-after-university" target="_blank">UK graduates: share your experience of applying for jobs after university</a></h2><div class="description"> Recruitment and Employment Confederation and KPMG’s Report on Jobs has found that permanent job placements have declined at the quickest rate in just over three years amid a weak economic outlook and reduced confidence among UK businesses. Recent graduates and those starting their careers are finding the search for employment.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 15:17:37 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/08/uk-graduates-share-your-experience-of-applying-for-jobs-after-university" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/audio/2023/aug/08/summer-picks-should-we-ban-artificial-grass-podcast" target="_blank">Summer picks: should we ban artificial grass? – podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> Madeleine Finlay speaks to Guardian feature writer Sam Wollaston and urban ecologist Prof Rob Francis about why people go for artificial grass, its environmental impact, and whether it’s time we rid ourselves of the idea of the perfect lawn altogether. Read about the plastic lawn backlash from this episode from April 2023.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 04:00:04 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/audio/2023/aug/08/summer-picks-should-we-ban-artificial-grass-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/08/the-legacy-of-sinead-oconnor-podcast" target="_blank">The legacy of Sinéad O’Connor – podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> Film-maker Kathryn Ferguson and journalist Simon Hattenstone share their memories of Sinéad O'Connor and reflect on her impact on music and society. Ferguson directed Nothing Compares, a 2022 documentary about the singer's life. She explains why O’Connor spoke out about abuse in the early 1990s when it was still taboo to do so.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 02:00:00 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/08/the-legacy-of-sinead-oconnor-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/audio/2023/aug/07/world-cup-england-nigeria-australia-denmark" target="_blank">Women’s Football Weekly: Lionesses find a way to win after James red card</a></h2><div class="description"> England beat Nigeria on penalties to reach the quarter-finals of the Women's World Cup. Lauren James will miss out after being sent off in the last 16 of the tournament. Andi Hickman, Faye Carruthers and Suzanne Wrack discuss the last three days of last-16 action.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 20:01:52 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/audio/2023/aug/07/world-cup-england-nigeria-australia-denmark" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/audio/2023/aug/07/efl-arsenal-shake-city-hoodoo-football-weekly-podcast" target="_blank">EFL back with a bang and Arsenal shake City hoodoo - Football Weekly podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> Football Weekly is a weekly football podcast from the Guardian. This week's episode is hosted by Max Rushden, Ben Fisher, George Elek, Sanny Rudravajhala and Sanny Rudra. Listen to the latest episode of our weekly podcast, Football Weekly, on BBC One and Sky Sports.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 12:17:18 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/audio/2023/aug/07/efl-arsenal-shake-city-hoodoo-football-weekly-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/07/how-hip-hop-gave-voice-to-a-generation-of-egyptians-hungry-for-change-podcast" target="_blank">How hip-hop gave voice to a generation of Egyptians hungry for change – podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> Music was vital to the early days of the Tahrir Square protests. The country is taking another authoritarian turn, that spirit of dissent cannot be extinguished, says The Guardian. Hip-hop gave voice to a generation of young Egyptians hungry for change, says the podcast podcast.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 04:00:29 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/07/how-hip-hop-gave-voice-to-a-generation-of-egyptians-hungry-for-change-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/the-outdated-commons-culture-will-endure-unless-parties-work-together" target="_blank">The outdated Commons culture will endure unless parties work together</a></h2><div class="description"> Labour’s Chris Bryant won’t be the last member to be sexually harassed by other MPs unless a better complaints procedure is brought in. Public sympathy for MPs is in short supply, and faith in them has been stretched to breaking point after a seemingly endless slew of sleaze scandals.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 17:45:19 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/the-outdated-commons-culture-will-endure-unless-parties-work-together" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/richard-nixon-plot-allende-chile-presidency" target="_blank">Files reveal Nixon role in plot to block Allende from Chilean presidency</a></h2><div class="description"> Newly declassified documents show Richard Nixon met with rightwing media mogul Agustín Edwards in September 1970 and discussed plans to foil socialist election-winner Salvador Allende. The documents are published in a new Spanish edition of the Pinochet files by archivist and writer Peter Kornbluh.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 17:49:46 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/richard-nixon-plot-allende-chile-presidency" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/08/krystsina-tsimanouskaya-athletics-career-poland-belarus-interview" target="_blank">Krystsina Tsimanouskaya: ‘I’m sure my career would be over if I was in Belarus now’</a></h2><div class="description"> Krystsina Tsimanouskaya has built a new life in Warsaw and won the right to run for Poland at this month’s world championships. The sprinter was ejected from the Belarus team at the Tokyo Olympics and fearing for her freedom if she returned home, sought refuge in Poland.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 11:20:19 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/08/krystsina-tsimanouskaya-athletics-career-poland-belarus-interview" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/china-philippines-dispute-could-escalate-into-superpower-conflict-say-analysts" target="_blank">China-Philippines dispute could escalate into superpower conflict, say analysts</a></h2><div class="description"> Chinese coastguards used water cannon on a Philippine boat. Concerns growing as China expands and modernises its military. China shows increasing aggression in its claims over the South China Sea and Taiwan. Joint drills with Russia have also heightened concern over military coordination between Beijing and Moscow.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 10:23:42 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/china-philippines-dispute-could-escalate-into-superpower-conflict-say-analysts" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/08/new-orleans-archbishop-gregory-aymond-protected-alleged-abusers" target="_blank">‘My prayerful support’: how the New Orleans archbishop hid ‘credibly accused’ abusers</a></h2><div class="description"> Memo reveals Gregory Aymond disregarded recommendations from board advisers to publicly label certain accused clerics as credibly suspected molesters. Board of advisers was set up to help determine the credibility of sexual abuse allegations made against clerics under his command. But, multiple times, he has demonstrated his comfort with disregarding recommendations from those advisers.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 10:00:32 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/08/new-orleans-archbishop-gregory-aymond-protected-alleged-abusers" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/aug/08/techscape-elon-musk-x-twitter-lawsuit-ccdh-hate-speech" target="_blank">TechScape: Why Elon Musk is taking trying to mute anti-hate-speech group</a></h2><div class="description"> Twitter alleges that the Center for Countering Digital Hate drove away advertisers – but CCDH and legal experts say otherwise. The social media company’s lawsuit against an anti-hate speech group is a key reason why Elon Musk bought Twitter for $44bn last year.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 10:52:39 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">tech</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/aug/08/techscape-elon-musk-x-twitter-lawsuit-ccdh-hate-speech" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global/2022/sep/20/sign-up-for-the-fashion-statement-newsletter-our-free-fashion-email" target="_blank">Sign up for the Fashion Statement newsletter: our free fashion email</a></h2><div class="description"> Style, with substance: what’s really trending this week, a roundup of the best fashion journalism and your wardrobe dilemmas solved, delivered straight to your inbox every Thursday. We’ve got something for you whether you love film, football, fashion or food.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 20 Sep 2022 11:06:20 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global/2022/sep/20/sign-up-for-the-fashion-statement-newsletter-our-free-fashion-email" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2019/jul/09/sign-up-for-word-of-mouth-the-best-of-guardian-food-every-week" target="_blank">Sign up for Word of Mouth: the best of Guardian Food every week</a></h2><div class="description"> A weekly email bringing you our best food writing, the latest recipes, seasonal eating ideas and must-read restaurant reviews. Sign up below to start receiving the best of our culinary journalism in one mouth-watering weekly email. We’ll send you latest recipes from Yotam Ottolenghi, Nigel Slater, Meera Sodha and all our star cooks.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 09 Jul 2019 08:19:21 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">health</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2019/jul/09/sign-up-for-word-of-mouth-the-best-of-guardian-food-every-week" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/gallery/2023/aug/08/portugal-wildfires-kittens-tuesday-best-photos" target="_blank">Portugal wildfires and tree-dwelling kittens: Tuesday’s best photos</a></h2><div class="description"> The Guardian's picture editors select photo highlights from around the world. Portugal's wildfires are the focus of this week's best photos. Portugal has been hit hard by wildfires in the past year and blamed for some of the country's worst fires in recent years. Click here for more from The Guardian.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 20